      <TermsOfUse><![CDATA[Carlos III University of Madrid permits Wifi Internet access only for the purposes of teaching and research activities, in accordance with the objectives, functions and responsibilities assigned to students, teaching and administration staff. 

It is expressly forbidden to change network addresses and use false identities in order to deceive third parties as to the identity of the sender of the message or the origin of any specific content. It is also forbidden to disseminate inappropriate content, such as: works subject to copyright, private personal or corporate data, detailed information about illegal items, pornography, gaming and betting, advertising, political propaganda, threatening or offensive messages, sexual or racial discrimination or harassment, the defence or support of terrorism and, in general, any content which represents an infringement of human rights or is to the detriment of a person's privacy, honour, image or dignity and the principles of the university institution.

Improper use of this resource may lead to the suspension of the service, without precluding disciplinary and legal action which might be taken. Carlos III University of Madrid reserves the right to initiate the appropriate action in those cases which, though not directly provided for in the present Agreement, are provided for in the Penal Code or in some other relevant regulations. In this respect, the following articles, among others, relating to damages and programs should be taken into account: articles 263 and 267 of the Penal Code; on intellectual property and concerning the regulations on data confidentiality.

]]></TermsOfUse>
